{"expireTime":9007200804686401000,"key":"transformer-remark-markdown-html-44d8af5a2a8aa28c92a568be6f0a3e89-gatsby-remark-graphvizgatsby-remark-code-titlesgatsby-remark-imagesgatsby-remark-responsive-iframegatsby-remark-autolink-headersgatsby-remark-prismjsgatsby-remark-copy-linked-filesgatsby-remark-smartypants-","val":"<p>VS Code is a truly great choice for your code editing needs. In this article, I‚Äôll show you some great tips and tricks, extensions, and more to maximize your productivity and get to what matters, building out great products. Some of these tips and tricks will make it even easier to contribute to the <a href=\"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby\">Gatsby core repo</a>, and help ensure your pull requests are ‚úÖ and accepted. That being said everything mentioned here can be applied to just about <em>any</em> JavaScript project.</p>\n<h2 id=\"editors---make-your-selection\"><a href=\"#editors---make-your-selection\" aria-label=\"editors   make your selection permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Editors - Make Your Selection</h2>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/f48df3da713cc64fcf0db20376fcaf15/263c7/color-wall.jpeg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 786px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 66.64999999999999%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px #ffffff;\"\n        alt=\"Lots of Available Options\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/f48df3da713cc64fcf0db20376fcaf15/00eda/color-wall.jpeg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/f48df3da713cc64fcf0db20376fcaf15/c1503/color-wall.jpeg 197w,\n/static/f48df3da713cc64fcf0db20376fcaf15/a941d/color-wall.jpeg 393w,\n/static/f48df3da713cc64fcf0db20376fcaf15/00eda/color-wall.jpeg 786w,\n/static/f48df3da713cc64fcf0db20376fcaf15/8e8ca/color-wall.jpeg 1179w,\n/static/f48df3da713cc64fcf0db20376fcaf15/f009a/color-wall.jpeg 1572w,\n/static/f48df3da713cc64fcf0db20376fcaf15/263c7/color-wall.jpeg 2000w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 786px) 100vw, 786px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>I know that there are as many choices for IDE editors and personal preferences as there are JS frameworks in existence (hint LOTS). I am not going to debate those here, this article will focus on <a href=\"https://code.visualstudio.com/\">VS Code</a>. It‚Äôs the editor I use and find it amazing for the Javascript and web development ecosystem. I was a long time holdout using Sublime Text, but once I gave VS Code a try I switched over within a day and haven‚Äôt looked back.</p>\n<h2 id=\"enough-talk-lets-get-started\"><a href=\"#enough-talk-lets-get-started\" aria-label=\"enough talk lets get started permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Enough Talk, Let‚Äôs get Started</h2>\n<p>First thing to do is <a href=\"https://code.visualstudio.com/download\">download VS Code</a> for your given OS platform. Ater opening the Editor and getting comfortable with the various screens, you‚Äôll notice one of the main views is the <a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/VSCode\">Extensions tab</a>. This is where the rubber meets the road, as these extensions <strong>really enhance</strong> the capabilities and productivity you‚Äôll realize using VS Code.</p>\n<h2 id=\"lets-talk-extensions\"><a href=\"#lets-talk-extensions\" aria-label=\"lets talk extensions permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Let‚Äôs Talk Extensions</h2>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7a5b5b7b6f9411f335fd87c5bff0314f/c1cca/install-meme.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 500px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 71.00000000000001%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px #ffffff;\"\n        alt=\"Install all the Extensions\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/7a5b5b7b6f9411f335fd87c5bff0314f/c1cca/install-meme.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/7a5b5b7b6f9411f335fd87c5bff0314f/84ee4/install-meme.jpg 197w,\n/static/7a5b5b7b6f9411f335fd87c5bff0314f/9cd63/install-meme.jpg 393w,\n/static/7a5b5b7b6f9411f335fd87c5bff0314f/c1cca/install-meme.jpg 500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>OK, not quite, if you browse the list you will notice there are <em>A LOT</em>. I‚Äôm going to review some popular ones that are applicable to contributing to the Gatsby.js GitHub repo.</p>\n<h3 id=\"-code-linting-and-formatting-\"><a href=\"#-code-linting-and-formatting-\" aria-label=\" code linting and formatting  permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>üö® Code linting and Formatting üö®</h3>\n<p>The main <a href=\"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby\">Gatsby GitHub repo</a> has configuration files in place already for <a href=\"https://eslint.org/\">ESLint</a> and <a href=\"https://prettier.io/\">Prettier</a>. VS Code has extensions for both of these, which makes development really easy.</p>\n<p>To get started, go to the Extensions View and <a href=\"https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/editor/extension-gallery#_browse-for-extensions\">search</a> for these plugins and press the green Install button for each. You may have to restart for the Extensions to take effect.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=esbenp.prettier-vscode\">Prettier - Code formatter</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=dbaeumer.vscode-eslint\">ESLint</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Now as you view, create, and modify files ESLint will display ‚Äúsquiggles‚Äù for warnings and errors in your files according to the existing rules already configured. You can correct any issues as you go.</p>\n<p>For Prettier, you have two options. You can run the Format manually, by bringing up the Command Palette <code class=\"language-text\">CMD + Shift + P</code> (<code class=\"language-text\">Ctrl + Shift + P</code> on Windows), then selecting <code class=\"language-text\">Format Document</code>. This will format the currently open File.</p>\n<p>The other option is to configure Prettier to Format on Save. You can enable the setting <code class=\"language-text\">editor.formatOnSave</code> by <a href=\"https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/getstarted/settings\">editing the Preferences</a> and applying this at the <em>User</em>, <em>Workspace</em>, or <em>Folder</em> level.</p>\n<h3 id=\"other-fun-plugins\"><a href=\"#other-fun-plugins\" aria-label=\"other fun plugins permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Other Fun Plugins</h3>\n<p>Of course once you start browsing the Extensions Marketplace you‚Äôll want to install additional plugins. Here is a short-list of <em>must-have</em> plugins you should consider installing.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=dzannotti.vscode-babel-coloring\">Babel ES6/ES7</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=eriklynd.json-tools\">JSON Tools</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=DavidAnson.vscode-markdownlint\">markdownlint</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=2gua.rainbow-brackets\">Rainbow Brackets</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=robertohuertasm.vscode-icons\">vscode-icons</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>You can take a look at my <a href=\"https://github.com/mikelax/dotfiles/tree/master/vscode\">‚Äúdotfiles‚Äù GitHub</a> for a README on the VS Code Extensions I am using along with editor settings.</p>\n<h2 id=\"-debugging-in-chrome-\"><a href=\"#-debugging-in-chrome-\" aria-label=\" debugging in chrome  permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>üöÄ Debugging in Chrome üöÄ</h2>\n<p>VS Code has a built-in debugger to enable proper runtime debugging, if you want to move past the <code class=\"language-text\">console.log</code> throughout your code. Use the following steps to be up and (debugging) in minutes.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Install the <a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=msjsdiag.debugger-for-chrome\">Debugger for Chrome</a> Extension for VS Code.</li>\n<li>In the Debug view, click the Debug Dropdown in the Panel and select the option <code class=\"language-text\">Add Config (projectname)</code>. This will create a <code class=\"language-text\">launch.json</code> file in your <code class=\"language-text\">.vscode</code> subfolder in the given project. Add the following to this file.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><em>NOTE</em>: You most likely will want to add the <code class=\"language-text\">.vscode</code> folder to your <code class=\"language-text\">.gitignore</code> file so it is not checked into source.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-code-title\">launch.json</div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"json5\"><pre class=\"language-json5\"><code class=\"language-json5\">{\n  version: &quot;0.2.0&quot;,\n  configurations: [\n    {\n      type: &quot;chrome&quot;,\n      request: &quot;launch&quot;,\n      name: &quot;Launch Chrome for Gatsby site&quot;,\n      url: &quot;http://localhost:8000&quot;,\n      webRoot: &quot;${workspaceFolder}&quot;,\n    },\n  ],\n}</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"conclusion\"><a href=\"#conclusion\" aria-label=\"conclusion permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Conclusion</h2>\n<p>In this article we have learned some of the basics about configuring and using VS Code for development on the Gatsby project. That being said, the Extensions and configuration discussed here can be applied to <em>any</em> modern JavaScript web project that <strong>may or may not use</strong> Gatsby.</p>\n<p>You may want to browse through the <a href=\"https://code.visualstudio.com/updates/\">VS Code Updates page</a> to see some of the recent features added. You‚Äôll notice they publish major updates monthly. It seems they are listening to the user community and continually adding features to the Editor and improvements to the user expereince.</p>\n<p>A great way to contribute is to browse the <a href=\"https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby/issues\">open issues on GitHub</a>, and find some that look interesting! Armed with some of the techniques I‚Äôve shown here today, authoring these fixes, features, and more will be a breeze thanks to some of the great features of VS Code.</p>\n<p>Do you use an Extension that I missed in this tutorial? Send send a message to <a href=\"https://twitter.com/mikelax\">@mikelax on Twitter</a> to let me know.</p>"}